org.emoncms

Class Feed

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.emoncms.Feed

  • public abstract class Feed
extends java.lang.Object
    The Feed class is used to communicate with an emoncms webserver and handle feed specific actions. An feed instance can be used to
    • Retrieve the latest and historical data.
    • Get configuration information.

    Feeds hold all their configuration fields in memory, but may be cleared to only hold their ID by calling clear(). Feed methods only need the ID to maintain their functionality and other resources may be released to save memory. Current values for all fields can be retrieved by calling load().
